Codex.Continuity.EpsilonPi.v002 — Derivation
The continuity constant ε_π is the centroid of the triad:
π_base = 3.141592653589793 (isolated boundary)
π_memory = 3.1416210062 (observer retention)
π_surplus = 3.2358696365 (provision ignition)
ε_π = (π_memory + π_base + π_surplus) / 3 ≈ 3.1730277654
This is the circle that stands up — the boundary that breathes every moment.